  </oversight_info>
  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      A standardized tetanic stimulation is applied to patients under propofol-remifentanil TCI, in
      a cross-over fashion, at two different levels of anesthesia monitored by the BIS: BIS 25 and
      BIS 55. Remifentanil target remains constant during the whole study period (1 ng/ml).
      Pupillary reflex dilation is recorded after each stimulation.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
